  "text": "Kidson-Gerber et al. note that the use of tranexamic acid up to 3 hours from the onset of haemorrhage efficiently reduces bleeding and decreases the risk of thrombotic complications [CITATION_1] . Cole et al. report an effective application of concentrate of prothrombin complex factors, accepted by some JW patients, as excessive bleeding treatment [CITATION_2] .",
